<paragraph blockId="12.[132,775,1950,2027]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">
HABITATS, NATURAL HISTORY AND DISTRIBUTION. — 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tornier" authorityYear="1902" class="Reptilia" family="Gekkonidae" genus="Lygodactylus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="conraui">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Lygodactylus conraui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a diurnal species inhabiting the West African savannahs and open forests from 
<collectingCountry box="[348,469,2003,2027]" name="Sierra Leone" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Sierra Leone</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[499,604,2003,2027]" name="Cameroon" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Cameroun</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="LOVERIDGE A." box="[615,771,2003,2027]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" pagination="1 - 469" refId="ref16101" refString="LOVERIDGE A. 1947. - Revision of the African lizards of the family Gekkonidae. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology 98: 1 - 469, pl. 1 - 7." type="journal article" year="1947">Loveridge 1947</bibRefCitation>
;
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="393" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[813,1457,944,1101]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">
<bibRefCitation author="PASTEUR G." box="[813,943,944,968]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" pagination="1 - 132" refId="ref16612" refString="PASTEUR G. 1965. - Recherches sur l'evolution des lygodactyles, lezards afro-malgaches actuels. Travaux de l'Institut Scientifique cherifien Zoologie, 29: 1 - 132, 1 carte, pl. I-XII." type="journal article" year="1965">Pasteur 1965</bibRefCitation>
). It was first reported to occur in 
<collectingCountry box="[1263,1313,945,969]" name="Togo" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Togo</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="BAUER A. M. &amp; TCHIBOZO S. &amp; PAUWELS O. S. G. &amp; GLET G." pageId="12" pageNumber="393" pagination="1 - 20" refId="ref14070" refString="BAUER A. M., TCHIBOZO S., PAUWELS O. S. G. &amp; LEN- GLET G. 2006. - A review of the gekkotan lizards of Benin, with the description of a new species of Hemidactylus (Squamata: Gekkonidae). Zootaxa 1242: 1 - 20." type="journal article" year="2006">
Bauer 
<emphasis box="[1410,1456,944,968]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">et al.</emphasis>
(2006)
</bibRefCitation>
for the locality of Zogbégan (specimen IRSNB 17158), situated inside ecological zone IV. Its further distribution in 
<collectingCountry box="[1407,1457,998,1022]" name="Togo" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Togo</collectingCountry>
is unknown. In South-Eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1118,1193,1024,1048]" name="Nigeria" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">Nigeria</collectingCountry>
, it occurs widely in forests (both swamped and dry; 
<bibRefCitation author="LUISELLI L. &amp; ENIANG E. A. &amp; AKANI G. C." box="[1058,1241,1050,1074]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" pagination="593 - 603" refId="ref16220" refString="LUISELLI L., ENIANG E. A. &amp; AKANI G. C. 2007. - Non-random structure of a guild of geckos in a fragmented, human altered African rainforest. Ecological Research 22: 593 - 603." type="journal article" year="2007">
Luiselli 
<emphasis box="[1135,1182,1050,1074]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
), and feeds mainly on adult Lepidoptera (
<bibRefCitation author="RUGIERO L. &amp; LUISELLI L. &amp; ENIANG E. A. &amp; AKANI G. C." box="[1001,1193,1077,1101]" pageId="12" pageNumber="393" pagination="91 - 96" refId="ref16955" refString="RUGIERO L., LUISELLI L., ENIANG E. A. &amp; AKANI G. C. 2007. - Diet of a guild of geckos in a fragmented, human altered African rainforest. African Journal of Herpetology 56 (1): 91 - 96." type="journal article" year="2007">
Rugiero 
<emphasis box="[1085,1132,1077,1101]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="393">et al.</emphasis>
2007
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
